frameDefinitions: The words in this frame describe situations in which a Perpetrator forcibly seizes control over a Victim's Vehicle to gain some end.  '' 'French farmers have hijacked a lorry and destroyed its load of strawberries.'
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
A Convoy consists of several Vehicles which move together to transport Cargo from a Source to a Goal.
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
A State_of_affairs is generally, or with regard to a particular Feature, representative of its class, which may be narrowed to a specific Comparison_set.
frameExamples: French farmers have <t>hijacked</t> a lorry and destroyed its load of strawberries.
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
A <t><fex name='con'>convoy</fex></t> of several dozen vehicles was stopped at the border for several hours while border guards inspected their cargo.
The Elan truly is an <t>unusual</t> car; the first and only Lotus with a front engined/front wheel drive layout, and the first new Lotus to be introduced since 1975.
listRoleDefinitions: This is the person (or other agent) who forcibly seizes control over a vehicle to gain some end.
This is the means of transportation which gets under the control of the perpetrator. Example: The terrorists hijacked <fex name='Vehicle'>the plane</fex>.
This role describes the people that are suffering as a result of the <fen>Perpetrator</fen>'s action.
This role is the being or entity that is injured by the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The constituent vehicles that make up the <fen>Convoy</fen>.
The group of vehicles transporting the <fen>Cargo</fen>.
The <fen>Cargo</fen> are the goods and/or individuals transported by the <fen>Convoy</fen>. This role also covers the intended use of the transported goods.

People and possibly other elements of the convoy who support and defend the transport of the <fen>Cargo</fen> are the <fen>Support</fen>. In military contexts, this typically consists of soldiers and military vehicles who provide defense for the conveying <fen>Vehicles</fen> and <fen>Cargo</fen>.
The general Place where the <fen>Convoy</fen> is operating.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
The state of affairs which is evaluated with regard to whether it exhibits the essential characteristics of a Comparison_set.
A property of the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> wherein it differs or is similar to members of a <fen>Comparison_set</fen>.
listRoleExamples: The rebels skyjacked a plane <fex>with 89 passangers</fex>.
The mysterious fighter attacked <fex>the guardsmen</fex> with a sabre.
<fex>The mysterious fighter</fex> attacked the guardsmen with a sabre.
<fex>As soon as he stepped out of the bar</fex> he was set upon by four men in ski-masks.
Then Jon-O's forces ambushed them <fex>on the left flank</fex> from a line of low hills.
Trained gunmen hijacked a <fex>20-car</fex> convoy headed for the city.
The southbound <fex>convoy</fex> of two vans and several armored vehicles arrived safely 10 hours after it had departed.
Trained gunmen hijacked a <fex>medical supply</fex> convoy headed for the city.
A military convoy <fex>of rebel gunmen</fex> stood between us and a large cache of weapons.
Convoys <fex>in Afghanistan</fex> have been hardest hit.
However I have always loved having an unusual <fex>name</fex> and I think it's a beautiful name. .
David Hasselhoff's daughters are normal <fex>in every way</fex>.
